blink_duration.description: How many seconds an eye blink will last.

bot_allow_grenades.description: If nonzero, bots may use grenades.

bot_allow_machine_guns.description: If nonzero, bots may use the machine gun.

bot_allow_pistols.description: If nonzero, bots may use pistols.

bot_allow_rifles.description: If nonzero, bots may use rifles.

bot_allow_rogues.description: If nonzero, bots may occasionally go 'rogue'. Rogue bots do not obey radio commands, nor pursue scenario goals.

bot_allow_shotguns.description: If nonzero, bots may use shotguns.

bot_allow_snipers.description: If nonzero, bots may use sniper rifles.

bot_allow_sub_machine_guns.description: If nonzero, bots may use sub-machine guns.

bot_auto_follow.description: If nonzero, bots with high co-op may automatically follow a nearby human player.

bot_auto_vacate.description: If nonzero, bots will automatically leave to make room for human players.

bot_autodifficulty_threshold_high.description: Upper bound above Average Human Contribution Score that a bot must be above to change its difficultyMin: -20.000000 Max: 20.000000

bot_autodifficulty_threshold_low.description: Lower bound below Average Human Contribution Score that a bot must be below to change its difficultyMin: -20.000000 Max: 20.000000

bot_chatter.description: Control how bots talk. Allowed values: 'off', 'radio', 'minimal', or 'normal'.

bot_chatter_use_rr.description: 0 = Use old bot chatter system, 1 = Use response rules

bot_controllable.description: Determines whether bots can be controlled by players

bot_coop_idle_max_vision_distance.description: Max distance bots can see targets (in coop) when they are idle, dormant, hiding or asleep.Min: -1.000000

bot_defer_to_human_goals.description: If nonzero and there is a human on the team, the bots will not do the scenario tasks.

bot_defer_to_human_items.description: If nonzero and there is a human on the team, the bots will not get scenario items.

bot_difficulty.description: Defines the skill of bots joining the game.  Values are: 0=easy, 1=normal, 2=hard, 3=expert.

bot_dont_shoot.description: If nonzero, bots will not fire weapons (for debugging).

bot_eco_limit.description: If nonzero, bots will not buy if their money falls below this amount.

bot_flipout.description: If nonzero, bots use no CPU for AI. Instead, they run around randomly.

bot_ignore_enemies.description: If nonzero, bots will ignore enemies (for debugging).

bot_ignore_players.description: Bots will not see non-bot players.

bot_join_after_player.description: If nonzero, bots wait until a player joins before entering the game.

bot_join_delay.description: Prevents bots from joining the server for this many seconds after a map change.

bot_join_in_warmup.description: Prevents bots from joining the server while warmup phase is active.

bot_join_team.description: Determines the team bots will join into. Allowed values: 'any', 'T', or 'CT'.

bot_loadout.description: bots are given these items at round start

bot_max_visible_smoke_length.description: Bots will see players through smoke clouds up to this length.

bot_max_vision_distance_override.description: Max distance bots can see targets.Min: -1.000000

bot_mimic.description: Bot uses usercmd of player by index.

bot_mimic_spec_buttons.description: +attack, +jump etc are used for spectator control instead of being passed on to spectated bot

bot_prefix.description:
This string is prefixed to the name of all bots that join the game.
<difficulty> will be replaced with the bot's difficulty.
<weaponclass> will be replaced with the bot's desired weapon class.
<skill> will be replaced with a 0-100 representation of the bot's skill.

bot_quota.description: Determines the total number of bots in the game.

bot_quota_mode.description:
Determines the type of quota.
Allowed values: 'normal', 'fill', and 'match'.
If 'fill', the server will adjust bots to keep N players in the game, where N is bot_quota.
If 'match', the server will maintain a 1:N ratio of humans to bots, where N is bot_quota.

bot_randombuy.description: should bots ignore their prefered weapons and just buy weapons at random?

bot_show_occupy_time.description: Show when each nav area can first be reached by each team.

bot_zombie.description: If nonzero, bots will stay in idle mode and not attack.

cl_clock_buffer_ticks.description: Clock sync will try to maintain an additional margin of N ticks.  This is intended to smooth over packet loss, and is a replacement for cl_interp_ratio / cl_interp.  This value is simply added to cl_clock_recvmargin_desired

cl_clock_correction.description: Enable/disable clock correction on the client.

cl_clock_recvmargin_adjust_limit_slowdow.description: Clock sync will not slow down time slower than N%Min: 66.000000 Max: 100.000000

cl_clock_recvmargin_adjust_limit_speedup.description: Clock sync will not speed up time faster than N%Min: 100.000000 Max: 150.000000

cl_clock_recvmargin_desired.description: Clock sync will try to maintain N ms margin between tick arrival and polling network.  The effective value is the sum of this and the time implied by cl_clock_buffer_ticks

cl_clock_recvmargin_minsamples_slowdown.description: Clock sync will not slow down unless we have N indicating samples

cl_clock_recvmargin_minsamples_speedup.description: Clock sync will not speed up unless we have N seconds of indicating samples

cl_clock_recvmargin_timeconstant_slowdow.description: Clock sync will remove 63.2% of the error in N seconds

cl_clock_recvmargin_timeconstant_speedup.description: Clock sync will remove 63.2% of the error in N seconds

cl_clock_recvmargin_window.description: Clock sync will use past N seconds

cl_connectionretrytime_p2p.description: Number of seconds over which to spread retry attempts for P2P.

cl_crosshairgap_useweaponvalue.description: If set to 1, the gap will update dynamically based on which weapon is currently equipped

voice_always_sample_mic.description: When enabled, open the voip audio input stream when the application launches.

voice_device_override.description: Default device used for voice capture.

voice_input_stallout.description: Time before we consider a mic stalled out and need to reset it.

voice_sequence_maximum_wait_time.description: When receiving packets out of sequence, wait this many seconds for missing sequences to arrive

voice_threshold.description: decibel threshold for how loud the talker's input signal is before we think they are talking.

voice_threshold_attack.description: Amount of time we buffer outgoing audio to detect an onset.

voice_threshold_delay.description: Amount of time the talker is silent before we infer that they are no longer talking.

voice_threshold_hold.description: Amount of time after the talker starts talking we should keep listening regardless of how loud they are speaking.

voice_threshold_ramp_min_db.description: A dB floor of when to stop transmitting packets, the volume between this and voice_threshold will still transmit packets to allow for volume ramping.

voice_vox.description: Voice chat uses a vox-style always on

voice_vox_current_peak.description: Current peak value (out of 64k) of the incoming voice stream

volume_fog_force_indirect_lpvs.description: Force use of LPVs for indirect lighting in fog

volume_fog_shadow_penumbra_multiplier.description: Penumbra size multiplier for shadow sampling, reduces fog shadow aliasing

weapon_accuracy_forcespread.description: Force spread to the specified value.

weapon_accuracy_reset_on_deploy.description: On deploy, forcibly reset weapon accuracy to zero.

weapon_air_spread_scale.description: Scale factor for jumping inaccuracy, set to 0 to make jumping accuracy equal to standingMin: 0.000000

weapon_auto_cleanup_time.description: If set to non-zero, weapons will delete themselves after the specified time (in seconds) if no players are near.

weapon_debug_inaccuracy_only_up.description: Force weapon inaccuracy to be in exactly the up direction

weapon_debug_max_inaccuracy.description: Force all shots to have maximum inaccuracy

weapon_debug_spread_show.description: Enables display of weapon accuracy; 1: show accuracy box, 3: show accuracy with dynamic crosshair

weapon_land_dip_amt.description: The amount the gun should dip when the player lands after a jump.

weapon_max_before_cleanup.description: If set to non-zero, will remove the oldest dropped weapon to maintain the specified number of dropped weapons in the world.

weapon_molotov_maxdetonateslope.description: Maximum angle of slope on which the molotov will detonateMin: 0.000000 Max: 90.000000

weapon_reticle_knife_show.description: When enabled will show knife reticle on clients. Used for game modes requiring target id display when holding a knife.

weapon_sound_falloff_multiplier.description: Scaling for falloff of weapon firing sounds

webapi_values_init_buffer_size.description: Initial buffer size for buffers in the WebAPIValues buffer pool

webapi_values_max_pool_size_mb.description: Maximum size in bytes of the WebAPIValues buffer pool

zoom_sensitivity_ratio.description: Additional mouse sensitivity scale factor applied when FOV is zoomed in.Min: 0.010000 Max: 3.000000
